\pard\plain \sa100\sb100\ql\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 I\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8217\'92ve been reflecting on why I started this group a few years ago. It is surely a struggle to try and harmonize these two books. The Urantia book is much easier for me to believe in because of it\u8217\'92s straight forward presentation of concepts and it\u8217\'92s very complex internal consistency. The Course in Miracles is much more abstract. It seems to be that way on purpose. Much like the way Jesus used parables to teach, he seems to use a method in the Course that is difficult to understand, very abstract. }
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \~I feel pretty certain now that the voice in the Course is that of Jesus. But it took me years to suspect that he was limited by the mind of Helen who transcribed it. Why would Jesus complement the Urantia revelation with a book that uses different terminology. Why would he say Sonship instead of God the Supreme? His use of the word Knowledge is different from the same word in the Urantia book. I now believe that he kept it simple and dealt with Helen directly in the same way he dealt with the apostles. He used Helen's understanding rather than trying to rearrange her mind. I am sure Helen\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8217\'92s job was hard enough as it was without having to digest the Urantia book while scribing the Course. I do believe the Course is meant to compliment the Urantia book. But why? }
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Before Jesus bestowal he was instructed not to write anything directly as it would become dogmatized. So he let others witness for him even though he knew they would be imperfect witnesses. I think he did the same thing in this instant. If he had given us a book with his own words as the revelators did, they would have become dogmatized. Helen was a scribe. Jesus referred to Helen as a scibe. This can be found in the notes before the edit. "NOTE: Scribes have a particular role in the Plan of Atonmenent, because they have the ability to EXPERIENCE revelations themselves, and also to put into words enough of the experience to serve as a basis for miracles."He also said this: "Scribes MUST learn Christ-control, to replace their former habits, which DID produce scarcity rather than abundance." Helen had to learn to work with Jesus to "put into words enough of the experience". This is very much a collaboration. So, it is our job to compare concepts and make a mental map of the terminology if we really want to understand the goal of the Course in relation to the Urantia book. }
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 The ultimate goal of the course is the elimination of fear and absolute forgiveness. This paragraph from the Urantia book says pretty much the same thing. }
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 2\~-\~(102:6.1)\~The philosophic\~elimination\~of\~religious\~fear\~and the steady progress\~of\~science add greatly to the mortality\~of\~false gods; and even though these casualties\~of\~man-made deities may momentarily befog the spiritual vision, they eventually destroy that ignorance and superstition which so long obscured the living God\~of eternal love. The relation between the creature and the Creator is a living experience, a dynamic religious faith, which is not subject to precise definition. To isolate part\~of\~life and call it religion is to disintegrate life and to distort religion. AND THIS IS JUST WHY THE GOD\~OF WORSHIP CLAIMS ALL ALLEGIANCE OR NONE.}
\par\plain \f1\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 The Course does require an absolute focus on forgiveness of all the Sonship. That is no easy task considering the evil we have on planet earth.}
