\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 The Urantia book warns us about a danger to civilization. \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'931\~-\~(111:4.3)\~The advances of true civilization are all born in this inner world of mankind. It is only the inner life that is truly creative. Civilization can hardly progress when the majority of the\~youth\~of any generation devote their interests and energies to the materialistic pursuits of the\~sensory\~or outer world.\u8221\'94 \~It goes on to warn us that \u8220\'93Any civilization is in jeopardy when three quarters of its\~youth\~enter materialistic professions and devote themselves to the pursuit of the\~sensory\~activities of the outer world.\u8221\'94 So we need at least one quarter of our youth interested in the inner world in order for civilization to survive. }
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Are we in jeopardy of going below that threshold? One quarter of America\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8217\'92s youth is no small number. Churches are declining in membership. Is it the youth ministers that kept civilization afloat all these years? And if the church is losing ground who will interest the next generation of youths to pursue a career focused on the inner life? I think the Urantia book and the Course in Miracles May help spark a revival in the coming years. We will need to interest the youth in this revival. }
